# KERNEL_VERSION -- authoritative version string for this kernel tool layer.
#
# Bump discipline (upstream kernel duty):
#   - Increment on EVERY change to any file under _tools/ before shipping.
#   - Use semver: MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH
#     * PATCH: bug-fix / no API or behaviour change.
#     * MINOR: new backward-compatible capability.
#     * MAJOR: breaking change in tool API or oracle.yml schema.
#   - The version here MUST match the tools_version recorded in
#     .kernel-manifest.json after `make manifest` is run.
#   - Never leave this at the same value while changing tool files --
#     version-string comparisons become meaningless if the version never moves.
#
# This file is read by manifest.render() (oracle_agent/manifest.py) so the
# tools_version in the manifest is always derived from this single source of
# truth rather than a hardcoded default.  The manifest's aggregate_sha256
# (which hashes every _tools file including this one) is the definitive
# integrity fingerprint; the version string is human-readable bookkeeping.
3.0.0
